        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(policy): recognize declared tool allowlists",
        "body": "Fixes #77801.\n\n## Summary\n- Treat materializable manifest-declared plugin tool names and plugin ids as known allowlist entries for diagnostics before the tools are materialized.\n- Treat enabled configured MCP server namespaces, including server-prefixed exact names/globs such as `paperless__*`, as known allowlist entries before bundled MCP tools are materialized.\n- Preserve typo/unavailable detection for disabled or denied declarations, so entries such as `papreless__*`, disabled MCP namespaces, denied MCP entries, and denied plugin tools still warn.\n\n## Scope\n- Internal tool-policy warning classification only.\n- No config schema/options, CLI flags, migrations, or plugin public API/surface changes.\n- Does not change actual tool filtering or materialization behavior.\n\n## ClawSweeper follow-up\n- Declared plugin context now mirrors runtime materialization gates: unavailable control-plane plugins, disabled plugin entries, `plugins.deny`, tool denylist entries, plugin group deny entries, and tool availability gates are excluded from the declared allowlist context.\n- Declared MCP context now ignores configured servers with `enabled: false`.\n- Declared MCP context now also applies explicit denylist handling: `tools.deny: [\"bundle-mcp\"]` and server-prefixed deny entries such as `paperless__*` prevent the MCP declaration from suppressing diagnostics.\n- Added regressions for disabled plugin tools, denied plugin tools, disabled MCP servers, disabled MCP namespace warning behavior, denied `bundle-mcp`, and denied MCP server namespace warning behavior.\n\n## Proof\nRedacted terminal proof from the policy pipeline path after the follow-up commits:\n\n```text\nenabled MCP namespace declared: no warnings\ntypo MCP namespace still warns: tools: tools.allow allowlist contains unknown entries (papreless__*). These entries won't match any tool unless the plugin is enabled.\ndisabled MCP namespace still warns: tools: tools.allow allowlist contains unknown entries (disabled__*). These entries won't match any tool unless the plugin is enabled.\ndenied bundle MCP still warns: tools: tools.allow allowlist contains unknown entries (bundle-mcp). These entries won't match any tool unless the plugin is enabled.\ndenied MCP namespace still warns: tools: tools.allow allowlist contains unknown entries (paperless__*). These entries won't match any tool unless the plugin is enabled.\nenabled browser plugin declared: no warnings\ndenied browser plugin still warns: tools: tools.allow allowlist contains unknown entries (browser). These entries are shipped core tools but unavailable in the current runtime/provider/model/config.\n```\n\n## Validation\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/tool-policy-pipeline.test.ts src/agents/tool-policy.plugin-only-allowlist.test.ts src/plugins/tools.optional.test.ts src/agents/agent-bundle-mcp-tools.request-boundary.test.ts --reporter=dot` - passed; 3 Vitest shards, 110 tests total.\n- `git diff --check` - passed.\n- `/home/giodl/src/openclaw-85529/node_modules/oxfmt/bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/agents/tool-policy-declared-context.ts src/agents/tool-policy-pipeline.test.ts` - passed.\n- `/home/giodl/src/openclaw-85529/node_modules/oxlint/bin/oxlint --tsconfig config/tsconfig/oxlint.core.json src/agents/tool-policy-declared-context.ts src/agents/tool-policy-pipeline.test.ts` - 0 warnings, 0 errors.\n- `git log --show-signature --format=\"%H %G? %s\" origin/main..HEAD` - all 3 commits have good signatures for `giodl73@gmail.com`.\n\nNote: The final signed follow-up commit used `--no-verify` because this WSL worktree's commit hook attempted `pnpm install` and aborted on an interactive modules purge prompt. The focused tests, formatter, linter, and whitespace checks above were run successfully before the signed push. No merge performed.",
